    "updated_at": "2015-06-20T18:54:18Z",
    "body": "If we can return from SIGSEGV and SIGBUS on some platforms, I support that option. For other platforms we should reset the mask as you suggest.\n\nI find it very important to be able to quickly identify a stack overflow, as to not raise confusion with way more scary cases of signals. As long as you stick with safe Rust, you should get friendly error messages.\n",
