    "created_at": "2024-10-21T21:57:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-10-21T21:57:36Z",
    "body": "Is current implementation the intended behavior? On Linux, rust processes don't dump core when receiving SIGSEGV or SIGBUS using e.g. \"kill -11 $(pidof process)\". Instead, they dump core the second time they receive SIGSEGV/SIGBUS (after the default signal handler has been restored). This is against the Linux semantic of those signals AFAIK. Typically a Linux process dumps core when receiving SIGSEGV.",
